### 3.2 Key IA decision: Services vs. Tech Manager

Services is the new flagship. Tech Manager is important but secondary. The nav, hero, and home page all need to reflect this. Tech Manager continues to have a great dedicated page — it just stops being the first thing visitors see.

### 3.3 Central Control integration positioning

Central Control shows up in two places:

1. **Integrations > Central Control** (standalone page explaining what it is, why it matters, and how the integration works)
2. **Within the Services page** (as the paid-tier capability that makes Services feel like magic)

The standalone integration page is important because tech-sophisticated buyers will search for "church production software with Central Control" and need a landing page that speaks their language.

