## 7. Build Sequence

This is a big scope. Phase it. Don't try to ship everything at once.

### Phase 1 — Positioning shift (ship in 2-3 weeks)

1. Rewrite home page hero and top sections
2. Update primary navigation
3. Add Services page (core sections, can expand later)
4. Add Volunteers page (core sections)
5. Update Tech Manager page positioning
6. Redirect and footer updates

At the end of Phase 1, the site is repositioned. Paid-tier Central Control integration story is teased but not fully landed.

### Phase 2 — Paid-tier depth (ship 2-3 weeks after Phase 1)

1. Central Control integration page (full depth)
2. Pricing page rebuild
3. Why Worship Metrics page
4. Platform Overview page update

At the end of Phase 2, the paid-tier story is fully landed and the site can convert paid customers.

### Phase 3 — Content and audience (ongoing)

1. Signal and Sanctuary landing page
2. Knowledge Base expansion (separate content project)
3. Case studies from design-partner churches
4. Blog or long-form editorial (separate content strategy)

### Phase 4 — Optimization (continuous)

1. A/B testing on hero and CTAs
2. Conversion funnel analysis
3. Page-level performance improvements
4. Iterative copy refinement based on user behavior

