## 11. Build Directive

Ship Phase 1 first. Don't wait for everything. Phase 1 alone — new hero, new nav, Services page, Volunteers page, Tech Manager reposition — meaningfully repositions the product and sets the stage for the paid-tier push in Phase 2.

When in doubt between aggressive repositioning and incremental polish, choose aggressive. The current site sells a product that is one feature of what we're actually building. Every day it stays that way is a day we're undersold.

Preserve what's working. Change what's wrong. Don't over-design. Let the product speak.